Package: fars
Type: Package
Title: Make a map of accident data per state
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2020-12-30
Authors@R: person("Anoushiravan", "Razmavar", 
    email = "anooshrz@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Inputs data from the US National Highway Traffic Safety 
    Administration's Fatality Analysis Reporting System and calculate 
    the number of accidents per state in a given year.It also makes a 
    map of each state and put pointers on it based on the geographical 
    positions of where accidents occurred. 
Depends: R(>= 4.0.2), 
    knitr(>= 1.30)
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: dplyr,
    tidyr,
    readr,
    maps,
    graphics,
    devtools,
    magrittr
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
suggests: rmarkdown,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
